    \begin{block}{Example}
        \textbf{SHA-256 Example:}
        Given an input message \( M \): "Hello, World!"
        The SHA-256 hash function will produce:
        \begin{equation}
            \text{Hash}(M) = \text{4d186321c1a7f0f354b297e8914ab240}
        \end{equation}
        (in hexadecimal format)
